## Overview

`HighlightedCodeBlock` extends `CodeBlock` with runtime syntax highlighting using Shiki. It loads the highlighter dynamically, so projects that don't use this component won't bundle Shiki.

- **CodeBlock** - Simple, no dependencies, for displaying code without highlighting
- **HighlightedCodeBlock** - Includes Shiki for syntax highlighting, tree-shakeable

## Basic Usage

Provide code and a language for automatic syntax highlighting.

```svelte preview title="TypeScript Highlighting"
<HighlightedCodeBlock
	language="typescript"
	code={`interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

function greet(user: User): string {
  return \`Hello, \${user.name}!\`;
}`}
/>
```

## Multiple Languages

Supports all languages supported by Shiki.

```svelte preview title="Rust"
<HighlightedCodeBlock
	language="rust"
	filename="main.rs"
	code={`fn main() {
    let numbers: Vec<i32> = (1..=10).collect();
    let sum: i32 = numbers.iter().sum();
    println!("Sum: {}", sum);
}`}
/>
```

```svelte preview title="Python"
<HighlightedCodeBlock
	language="python"
	filename="fibonacci.py"
	code={`def fibonacci(n: int) -> int:
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2)

# Generate first 10 fibonacci numbers
for i in range(10):
    print(fibonacci(i))`}
/>
```

```svelte preview title="Svelte"
<HighlightedCodeBlock
	language="svelte"
	filename="Counter.svelte"
	code={`<script lang="ts">
  let count = $state(0);
  const doubled = $derived(count * 2);
</script>

<button onclick={() => count++}>
  Count: {count} (doubled: {doubled})
</button>`}
/>
```

## Custom Themes

Use different Shiki themes for various color schemes.

```svelte preview title="GitHub Dark (Default)"
<HighlightedCodeBlock
	language="javascript"
	theme="github-dark"
	code={`const add = (a, b) => a + b;
console.log(add(2, 3));`}
/>
```

## Without Line Numbers

Hide line numbers for shorter snippets.

```svelte preview title="No Line Numbers"
<HighlightedCodeBlock
	language="bash"
	showLineNumbers={false}
	code="bun add ukiyoe shiki"
/>
```

## Inline Code

Inline highlighted code within text.

```svelte preview title="Inline Usage"
<Text>
	Use <HighlightedCodeBlock inline language="typescript" code="$state()" /> for reactive state,
	and <HighlightedCodeBlock inline language="typescript" code="$derived()" /> for computed values.
</Text>
```

